{"type":"message","id":"7a47aedd","parentId":"6fa520a2","timestamp":"2026-03-31T10:18:47.191Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"用户问的是WiFi协议中，MU（Multi-User）MIMO场景是否支持puncture（打孔）。这是一个WiFi协议的技术问题。\n\n让我先搜索一下相关信息。","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_148841534abb430887a162c7","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"WiFi MU-MIMO puncture preamble puncturing 802.11ax 802.11be"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-43-133-33-215-3000","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":26226,"output":104,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26330,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774952318570,"responseId":"ced856e11118071504421f3ef6d681b9"}}
{"type":"message","id":"faedff9f","parentId":"7a47aedd","timestamp":"2026-03-31T10:18:48.837Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_148841534abb430887a162c7","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"WiFi MU-MIMO puncture preamble puncturing 802.11ax 802.11be\",\n  \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n  \"count\": 5,\n  \"tookMs\": 1644,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"tavily\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1a27b999b6bb0d31\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n[PDF] Physical Layer Implementation Analysis of IEEE 802.11be Preamble ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1a27b999b6bb0d31\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://assets-eu.researchsquare.com/files/rs-5319858/v1_covered_e46b4afe-1a13-42f5-963b-965c135d47ca.pdf\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d2086303e9210d7e\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nPhysical Layer Implementation Analysis of IEEE 802.11be Preamble Puncturing in SU Transmission Hamidou DEMBELE Wi¬rst https://orcid.org/0009-0007-8735-0191 Sih-Yu Chou Wi¬rst Research Article Keywords: WLAN, IEEE 802.11be, 802.11ax, Wi-Fi 7/6, preamble puncturing, single-user, wider-bandwidth, channel bonding, PHY/MAC layers, OFDMA, spectral e®ciency Posted Date: November 26th, 2024 DOI: https://doi.org/10.21203/rs.3.rs-5319858/v1 License:   This work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License. While the implementation of preamble puncturing has been demon-strated in multiple-users (MU) scenarios with orthogonal frequency division multiple access (OFDMA) in IEEE 802.11ax (Wi-Fi 6) downlink transmissions, its feasibility, especially for single-user (SU) transmission at the physical (PHY) layer, including resource units (RUs) aggregation in IEEE 802.11be, remains under investigation, with ongoing research eﬀorts. Keywords: WLAN, IEEE 802.11be, 802.11ax, Wi-Fi 7/6, preamble puncturing, single-user, wider-bandwidth, channel bonding, PHY/MAC layers, OFDMA, spectral eﬃciency.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"d2086303e9210d7e\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.843393\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"67d1a38c966f18c1\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nOFDM:Advanced:Preamble Puncturing:Bitmap Property - NI\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"67d1a38c966f18c1\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.ni.com/docs/en-US/bundle/rfmx-wlan-prop/page/rfmxwlanprop/attra00030.html?srsltid=AfmBOorY8s_qoyFM2XtoYiVZHrfk455tw1lgFi39-AWURW0sg67T5Gjf\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f439e4c9a994bd87\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nSpecifies the punctured 20 MHz sub-channels in the 802.11ax MU PPDU or the 802.11be MU PPDU signal when preamble puncturing is enabled. The binary\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"f439e4c9a994bd87\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.83549726\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"01fb5d0a01556322\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n[DOC] 11-19/1262 - IEEE Mentor\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"01fb5d0a01556322\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://mentor.ieee.org/802.11/dcn/19/11-19-1262-19-00be-specification-framework-for-tgbe.docx\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"725c0dc91812d0b6\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n802.11be STA can recognize the preamble puncturing pattern it needs by using the BW field and puncturing information of U-SIG and/or EHT-SIG field in\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"725c0dc91812d0b6\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.7300017\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e0f2f84e7d592101\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n802.11be Waveform Generation - MATLAB & Simulink - MathWorks\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e0f2f84e7d592101\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.mathworks.com/help/wlan/ug/802-11be-waveform-generation.html\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e5026cf3a6bdc6ce\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nA full-band non-OFDMA packet is an EHT MU packet that contains the transmission of a single user or multiple users in an MU-MIMO configuration over the full channel bandwidth. The non-OFDMA packet format supports single-user and MU-MIMO packet transmission in large MRUs. The EHT-USIG field of an EHT MU packet carries the punctured sub-channel indication for a non-OFDMA transmission. Create an OFDMA configuration for a 20 MHz EHT MU packet with two 52-tone RUs, one 106+26-tone MRU, and one user per RU, as defined by allocation index 47. The selection of `X1` to `X6` configures the appropriate number of users through an allocation index in the 20 MHz subchannel and determines which EHT-SIG content channel signals the users on the 996+484-tone RU. Create a 20 MHz OFDMA configuration with four RUs with a user in each RU using allocation index 52. RU allocation and EHT-SIG user signaling for 242-, 484-, 996-, and 2x996-tone RUs. MRU allocation and EHT-SIG user signaling for allocation >=80 MHz.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e5026cf3a6bdc6ce\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.43194416\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fcc47f26d6d7b2d9\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\n[PDF] ©Rohde & Schwarz; IEEE 802.11be technology introduction\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fcc47f26d6d7b2d9\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://8928696.fs1.hubspotusercontent-na1.net/hubfs/8928696/20240507%20-%20Rohde%20&%20Schwarz%20IEEE%20802-11be%20Whitepaper.pdf\",\n      \"snippet\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fd0600d294e7c331\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe IEEE 802.11be PHY is very similar to the PHY defined in the highly successful IEEE 802.11ax standard. For example,. IEEE 802.11be will support MU-MIMO,\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"fd0600d294e7c331\\\">>>\",\n      \"score\": 0.41492313\n    }\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"WiFi MU-MIMO puncture preamble puncturing 802.11ax 802.11be","provider":"tavily","count":5,"tookMs":1644,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"tavily","wrapped":true},"results":[{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"1a27b999b6bb0d31\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n[PDF] Physical Layer Implementation Analysis of IEEE 802.11be Preamble ...\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"1a27b999b6bb0d31\">>>","url":"https://assets-eu.researchsquare.com/files/rs-5319858/v1_covered_e46b4afe-1a13-42f5-963b-965c135d47ca.pdf","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d2086303e9210d7e\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nPhysical Layer Implementation Analysis of IEEE 802.11be Preamble Puncturing in SU Transmission Hamidou DEMBELE Wi¬rst https://orcid.org/0009-0007-8735-0191 Sih-Yu Chou Wi¬rst Research Article Keywords: WLAN, IEEE 802.11be, 802.11ax, Wi-Fi 7/6, preamble puncturing, single-user, wider-bandwidth, channel bonding, PHY/MAC layers, OFDMA, spectral e®ciency Posted Date: November 26th, 2024 DOI: https://doi.org/10.21203/rs.3.rs-5319858/v1 License:   This work is licensed under a Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License. While the implementation of preamble puncturing has been demon-strated in multiple-users (MU) scenarios with orthogonal frequency division multiple access (OFDMA) in IEEE 802.11ax (Wi-Fi 6) downlink transmissions, its feasibility, especially for single-user (SU) transmission at the physical (PHY) layer, including resource units (RUs) aggregation in IEEE 802.11be, remains under investigation, with ongoing research eﬀorts. Keywords: WLAN, IEEE 802.11be, 802.11ax, Wi-Fi 7/6, preamble puncturing, single-user, wider-bandwidth, channel bonding, PHY/MAC layers, OFDMA, spectral eﬃciency.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"d2086303e9210d7e\">>>","score":0.843393},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"67d1a38c966f18c1\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nOFDM:Advanced:Preamble Puncturing:Bitmap Property - NI\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"67d1a38c966f18c1\">>>","url":"https://www.ni.com/docs/en-US/bundle/rfmx-wlan-prop/page/rfmxwlanprop/attra00030.html?srsltid=AfmBOorY8s_qoyFM2XtoYiVZHrfk455tw1lgFi39-AWURW0sg67T5Gjf","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"f439e4c9a994bd87\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nSpecifies the punctured 20 MHz sub-channels in the 802.11ax MU PPDU or the 802.11be MU PPDU signal when preamble puncturing is enabled. The binary\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"f439e4c9a994bd87\">>>","score":0.83549726},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"01fb5d0a01556322\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n[DOC] 11-19/1262 - IEEE Mentor\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"01fb5d0a01556322\">>>","url":"https://mentor.ieee.org/802.11/dcn/19/11-19-1262-19-00be-specification-framework-for-tgbe.docx","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"725c0dc91812d0b6\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n802.11be STA can recognize the preamble puncturing pattern it needs by using the BW field and puncturing information of U-SIG and/or EHT-SIG field in\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"725c0dc91812d0b6\">>>","score":0.7300017},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e0f2f84e7d592101\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n802.11be Waveform Generation - MATLAB & Simulink - MathWorks\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e0f2f84e7d592101\">>>","url":"https://www.mathworks.com/help/wlan/ug/802-11be-waveform-generation.html","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e5026cf3a6bdc6ce\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nA full-band non-OFDMA packet is an EHT MU packet that contains the transmission of a single user or multiple users in an MU-MIMO configuration over the full channel bandwidth. The non-OFDMA packet format supports single-user and MU-MIMO packet transmission in large MRUs. The EHT-USIG field of an EHT MU packet carries the punctured sub-channel indication for a non-OFDMA transmission. Create an OFDMA configuration for a 20 MHz EHT MU packet with two 52-tone RUs, one 106+26-tone MRU, and one user per RU, as defined by allocation index 47. The selection of `X1` to `X6` configures the appropriate number of users through an allocation index in the 20 MHz subchannel and determines which EHT-SIG content channel signals the users on the 996+484-tone RU. Create a 20 MHz OFDMA configuration with four RUs with a user in each RU using allocation index 52. RU allocation and EHT-SIG user signaling for 242-, 484-, 996-, and 2x996-tone RUs. MRU allocation and EHT-SIG user signaling for allocation >=80 MHz.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"e5026cf3a6bdc6ce\">>>","score":0.43194416},{"title":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"fcc47f26d6d7b2d9\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\n[PDF] ©Rohde & Schwarz; IEEE 802.11be technology introduction\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"fcc47f26d6d7b2d9\">>>","url":"https://8928696.fs1.hubspotusercontent-na1.net/hubfs/8928696/20240507%20-%20Rohde%20&%20Schwarz%20IEEE%20802-11be%20Whitepaper.pdf","snippet":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"fd0600d294e7c331\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nThe IEEE 802.11be PHY is very similar to the PHY defined in the highly successful IEEE 802.11ax standard. For example,. IEEE 802.11be will support MU-MIMO,\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"fd0600d294e7c331\">>>","score":0.41492313}]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774952328837}}
{"type":"message","id":"837ef83a","parentId":"faedff9f","timestamp":"2026-03-31T10:19:00.928Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"从搜索结果看，有一些关于preamble puncturing的信息。让我获取更详细的内容，特别是关于MU-MIMO场景下是否支持puncture的信息。\n\n从第一个结果可以看出，在802.11ax中，preamble puncturing已经在MU场景中实现了（特别是OFDMA下行传输）。但用户问的是MU-MIMO场景，我需要更具体的信息。\n\n让我获取NI文档和MathWorks的文档来了解更多细节。","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_015fda3c67ce49ac966ceecb","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://www.ni.com/docs/en-US/bundle/rfmx-wlan-prop/page/rfmxwlanprop/attra00030.html","extractMode":"markdown"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_49a365a2c42741189627c6d6","name":"web_fetch","arguments":{"url":"https://www.mathworks.com/help/wlan/ug/802-11be-waveform-generation.html","extractMode":"markdown"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"custom-43-133-33-215-3000","model":"glm-5","usage":{"input":28166,"output":262,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":28428,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774952328838,"responseId":"98c679f7968209871f4e3ad2705614d6"}}
